# TEMPLATE: .htaccess.env.example
# If you cannot set environment variables in your hosting panel, you can create a local file
# named `.htaccess.env` (NOT versioned) and put SetEnv lines there. Then include it in
# your main `.htaccess` via `Include .htaccess.env` if allowed by your host.
# WARNING: prefer panel env variables or .env outside webroot over storing secrets in .htaccess.

# Example (uncomment and fill with real values if you must use this approach):
# SetEnv EFI_CLIENT_ID "your-client-id"
# SetEnv EFI_CLIENT_SECRET "your-client-secret"
# SetEnv EFI_PIX_KEY "your-pix-key"
# SetEnv EFI_WEBHOOK_TOKEN "your-webhook-token"
# SetEnv EFI_CERTIFICATE_PATH "/home/usuario/secrets/producao-573055-petfinder.pem"

# Notes:
# - If your provider supports `Include` in .htaccess you can keep `.htaccess.env` outside VCS
# - Do NOT commit `.htaccess.env` with real secrets
